##"Get something" : Rock and roll fans who use their early bird spirit as a financial aid

Vicechina  

Function description, different color vision

Tu Junnan (better known as TU, the lead singer of the band "Dulaika")'s donation diary appeared in friends' circles on the eve of the Lunar New Year. As in previous years, he did not go back to spend the Spring Festival with his family and stayed in Beijing alone. He had planned to return to Nanchang in March to be with his parents, but could not return this year because of the outbreak.

Alone at home, he couldn't care less about the singing of reunion and Glittering Days on New Year's Eve. All seven core members of get something going were busy, and the group, a spontaneous group of rock fans, issued their first aid package to Hubei, 500 medical disposable masks, a day after the city was shut down in Wuhan, 1,800 medical rubber gloves, 100 pairs of goggles, the recipient is Huazhong University of Science and Technology Union Hospital.

##

As usual, the 2020 Spring Festival gala, "a night to remember, " played out on television, and the growing number of news stories about the epidemic on social media played devil's advocate. At 10 a.m. on the morning of the Lunar New Year's Day twenty-nine, Wuhan was the first isolated island to be sealed off from other counties and cities in Hubei Province. Disease and death are happening all around us, and on New Year's Eve, at least 50 million people in Hubei Province don't care what's on their TV screens.

Little Tu's micro blog often help transfer some help, mostly music FANS@TU Junnan, with the caption "Little Tu help. ". That's how "get something" started.

"One of the promoters was a fan of Duleka who wanted to ask me if I could help retweet it on Weibo, and I was pulled into the group. ". Xiaotu found that the group never met friends eager to send support for the epidemic area, but the lack of planning methods, empty enthusiasm seems to be enough. Fukurai, Goth, Koala, OA, Oda, Az√©, and Tu were all "Internet friends" who did not know each other well; but the epidemic was intense and could not be delayed. Little Tu felt that there must be a reasonable shaping of working methods, began to directly participate in the material collection and donation organization work.

They needed to find a way to feel like themselves -- After all, seven people had limited abilities, and the Gregorian calendar was starting to run out at the end of January. It was easy to give, but hard to buy. They worried that a large number of donations in the hands but can not buy goods, and ultimately chose the "first source of goods and logistics, determine the need for money, and then a dollar to buy links in micro-shop crowdfunding" approach.

"We don't raise money in advance, so the flow of funds is not very big, " Tu said. "The advantage is that every amount of money is spent, and every single one can be checked. We also choose small hospitals where medical resources are relatively scarce to help. "

It's a viable model. They share information with friends in their neighborhood volunteer group to find suppliers who can still produce and ship goods, and with a group of 500 people on Wechat, which is filled with enthusiastic strangers or music fans, years of performance experience let them put on "early bird tickets" posture, rush to buy hair in the group of "one-yuan link, " Xiaotu said "sometimes seven or eight thousand links in half a minute. "

I tried to fight off many fans to see if I could do it, but I failed. Just filling out a delivery address and returning to the page shows "sold out. ". In order to save time, my address was entered in the simplest way, accurate only to Chaoyang District, and typing took only two minutes.

I didn't get this one.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"It's not sold out yet, let's go! " And "ORGANIZERS SUCK! " , Said Xiao Tu, referring to the 500-person crowd, where fans of the show compete for tickets with "Industry Slang" to dominate the group chat, which is made up of enthusiasm and love, it's a bit of a happy ending.

Let's see how the crowd of 500 at get something is doing. Photo by Junnan Tu

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Limited by the size of the purchase, "get something" has not opened two groups, before the operation has been in the group of 500 people chat. "It's enough to have 500 warm, stable friends to support you. ".

However, it is no longer easy to assist Hubei province because of the problems of unified distribution of materials and logistics. After I finished reading Tu's donation log on February 2, there were no updates in the next few days. As he put it, we also know very well that when things get tough, things don't move forward. The time of national rework is delayed again and again, Hubei controls more strictly, each group chat in mobile phone is hearsay news, true or false. When I asked Tu what he was going to do, he said, "We may have to change direction. ".

On the night of February 8th, a new link to a micro-store sale finally reappeared on friendagenda. More than three o'clock in the morning, Little Tu also finally updated the donation log again, with apparently blocked many times complained, "how to donate something I flee. ". The keyword place name can no longer appear in the main body of the micro-blog, so he has to change it into a code name that everyone can understand. I was relieved, but at the same time I felt helpless. It was just a donation log.

During the five days, they decided to open the "two groups" and switch their donation targets to the provinces around Hubei, where the epidemic also needs attention, such as Henan, Anhui and Jiangxi. At the same time, they also do the docking of resources and information, to synchronize larger supplies to neighborhood groups, but also for the ability to provide a large number of donations to friends channel.

As of February 8,2020, make something fans have raised and actually spent 43,630 yuan for medical supplies such as masks, medical gloves, goggles, protective masks, hand sanitizer and shoe covers, it was successfully sent to Tongji Medical College Union Hospital, Xiaogan Central Hospital, Xiangyang Central Hospital, Xiantao First People's hospital, Yichang second hospital, Yichang Third Hospital, Jingzhou Central Hospital, yellow stone colored hospital, Wufeng Tujia Autonomous County People's Hospital, Huangmei County People's Hospital, Qichun County People's Hospital, Wuhan Steel General Hospital, Xiaogan Central Hospital, Xiangyang Central Hospital, Xiangyang Chinese Medicine Hospital, Xiangyang People's Hospital, the General Hospital of Huangzhou, the First People's Hospital and the main hospital of New Orleans.

That may not seem like much in a pandemic, but a flame can be seen and feel the heat. Doodle keeps track of their donations in the donation log. I have taken fragments of these logs, which record how a feeble but luminous and hot flame moved slowly, and how, in the face of the declining reality, it withstood the sighs and disappointments of the heart, and poured out its passion with the first kindness, hang in there.

To Chun Nam's donation diary (excerpt)

24 January

Today is the first day of the group's formation, and most of the time is spent in internal discussions to determine the donation process, mode and sourcing. Gathering today's information and lessons from all sides, we hope to provide a reference for others who want to do something about it, as well as support for our fellow citizens caught in the middle of a COVID-19 epidemic and panic.

The seven of US determined the Division of Labor, including the collection of summary Information, direct contact with the manufacturer, payment purchase, bookkeeping, information management, publicity and convening. A specific programme of work has been defined (including how to effectively and rationally raise funds as a voluntary civil society organization) . Our process is: Network to identify material needs-contact hospitals to confirm the acceptance of social donations-call manufacturers-purchase orders-in the group to announce the amount of fund-raising.

Since we are not an official or official organization, each fund raised is based on the actual amount of goods needed, collected in the group. In order to control the amount limit and we all have the opportunity to help, we finally decided to use the micro-shop payment method (I used my own band's micro-shop, on the new merchandise, a unit price of one yuan, the maximum inventory for the total amount) , this is also good post directly from the background copy public.

25 January

Masks and protective clothing have been basically distributed by the state, which is a good thing, so we focused on other supplies. It's easier to find than masks, goggles, and protective clothing, which are among the most scarce items, like shoes, gloves, and medical caps, and they're just as much in demand. As we were reminded that disinfectants and alcohol were difficult to transport, and we had no conditions, we dropped them first.

Today, in addition to the growing volume of donations, links have been established with other voluntary civil society organizations. Learning from their work methods, and sharing resources and information, helps to avoid the need to do the same things in the same place, so that everyone's priorities are a little clearer.

26 January

Although it's only the third day, from the point of view of a completely spontaneous volunteer group, the changes we observe are not insignificant. A lot of teams are eating dust. It's getting harder and harder to find core supplies like masks and Hazmat suits, and we and a few other teams are getting a lot of unfilled orders. We all felt that this volunteer work, which had been intended to last a long time, might soon come to an end. The support of the helpless people is just a supplement to the existence of reason, but only when the action can stop, before that, how much to do, after all, there are too many not by ENZER's corner.

After three days, we were pretty sure that the current model was viable, albeit slow and small, and at least stable and effective. In addition to Xiangyang, Xiaogan, and Myrtle, we tried today to get in touch with eight smaller hospitals, sending some of their shoe covers, and will continue to collect other supplies for them tomorrow. Today is the day we handle the largest total amount of money, there are more than 10,000, did not expect to participate in fund-raising enthusiasm on the third day, very moved and very encouraged. Hope that no matter how the situation changes, how the crowd split, this is willing to unconditionally swim for the suffering of the compatriots to do something. Don't close your red eyes. Do what you can, even if it's just a little bit. Do your best. Don't lose heart.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
28-29 January

All extraordinary times are normal times. All Normal Times are extraordinary times. Save your strength.

Private donations to Hubei, including our group, have slowed or stalled. Material more and more difficult to find, we have to varying degrees of unqualified resources, logistics, coupled with many people in the malicious price and sales of fake goods, these two days of work is also a little more cautious.

We have to admit that enthusiasm has a tendency to wane (either actively or involuntarily) . With more and more tragedies and less and less to do, it seems that young people, accustomed to the false sense of engagement that comes with pressing the forward button on public events, are once again letting the initial energy get the better of them. There's no criticism here, and I think that's very normal today. At least I do that myself.

But, my lords, the plague will not go away so soon, and whether it touches itself this time or not, it is soaking us. If we are not prepared for The Foolish Old Man Removes the Mountain, we are likely to forget them and get used to them before they are over, and then the enthusiasm fades and only the truly suffering continue to die.

The thing about "passion" is that it's a good place to start, but it's hard to keep going. Without the values that come from deep conviction (the need for true self-improvement) , and the enthusiasm that sustains our actions over the long term, we can only breastfeed through successive triumphs, which in most cases is impossible. Don't doubt the motives of anyone involved in positive action, which is also disloyal to the original idea of "wanting the world to be better. ". Of course there are times of depression and doubt, even most of the time. Learn to acknowledge this, but don't use it as a slam dunk.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
30 -- 31 January

Volunteer groups that started giving in the first few days of the same period have stopped or are planning to stop. However, there are also many new volunteer organizations, some continuing to relay to Hubei, there are also rescue local hospitals, very moved. Civil voluntary organizations still want to help each other, contact with the information is relatively much, should try to convey to people around.

Our donations have been going on for more than a week, and we've all been a little bit worried about the lack of staying power, but I think it's going to be okay. With the resumption of work and classes, we will naturally draw away slowly, a little bit slow down is normal, sustained force. We all have to do what we can to make it work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
1-2 February

Not much has been done in these two days, everyone is tired in different degree, plus the difficult problem of finding materials and logistics. In many cases, we need to get the "letter of request" or other documents from the hospital before we can ship the goods, and a safe passage on the way.

A total of three batches of materials were purchased in these three days, namely, Hand Sanitizer, protective clothing and goggles. All three batches of materials were donated to Huangzhou General Hospital. In addition, the medical gloves we purchased on January 29 have been received by all six hospitals except Qichun County People's Hospital. If people later see that I didn't update the donation log for that day, it's probably because we didn't make any progress on that day, so we moved it to the back and put it together. Whatever happens, write more or less, and the donation journal will continue to circulate as a public notice, not quietly, until it is all over or done with. Thank you. Please continue to monitor, advise and motivate.

3-8 February

Because we wanted to make sure that every dollar was paid, and because we were worried that the operation, like so many things, would be too big and too small, we hadn't brought in any new groups since we filled our first fund-raising group on January 24, i want to concentrate on what I can do with it. But we can not let this stop in the "natural disappearance" , here nothing is really "natural" . We want to make it a really long term thing, in our way, at least in terms of civilian assistance, to get to the end with as many people as possible.

Want to pull a group again, not out of expanding the volume, want to "do a tough" consideration, but out of the above-mentioned intentions and principles. Because we want to fight a really long war, in the longer term, the number of people is the same, the burden falls on the existing people are more heavy, which is not conducive to sustainable.

All the pictures in this article are from Junnan Tu

So, if you have the heart to continue to pay close attention to the situation, the flow of water to participate in our material donation activities, you can join us two groups. Rock fans are the best. It doesn't matter if they're not. In addition to raising money, you can also help us find the right supplies, or start your own action.

Resistance to the outbreak may take a long time, but from the beginning, the plan was to hold out until the last minute. "As in the beginning, we're not trying to do anything big or anything big, but we're trying to do what ordinary people can do before the disaster is over: Get something done. It shouldn't stop until it's over. "
